C. Color System

    Extend the current color system.

    No green/red for favorite.
    Color reserved for future directional change only.

D. Behavior Rules

    Probability rounded to nearest whole %

    Moneyline rounded to nearest 5

    Moneyline derived from probability (zero-vig)

    If 47%–53% → show “Even” instead of moneyline

    No separators between forecast and signals

    Sensitivity hidden in this version

2️⃣ UX Details Document
    Tone

    Institutional

    Analytical

    Quiet authority

    No emotional reinforcement

    No hype

    Hierarchy Rules

    Probability dominates everything.

    Moneyline reinforces probability.

    Structural metrics explain forecast.

    Ledger provides empirical grounding.

    Eye flow:

    Top-left → Probability → Moneyline → Right grid → Ledger.

    Cognitive Design Principles

    Numeric-first design

    Tabular alignment

    Baseline rhythm consistency

    Controlled luminance hierarchy

    No decorative UI elements

    Interaction Behavior

    Future interactions allowed:

    Tap ledger → expand to full scroll view

    Tap metric label → tooltip explanation

    Long press moneyline → formula explanation

    But default screen remains static and clean.

    Accessibility

    Minimum contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for labels

    7:1 for numeric values

    Tap targets minimum 44px height

    Dark theme OLED optimized

    Performance

    No gradients

    No blur

    No heavy shadows

    Static layout (GPU friendly)



